label: Engineer
description: Licensed professional engineer who performs engineering services, makes technical decisions, and has professional obligations to uphold ethical standards
text_references: As members of this profession, engineers are expected to exhibit the highest standards of honesty and integrity
Engineers, in the fulfillment of their professional duties, shall:
Engineers shall hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public

label: Public
description: General population whose safety, health, and welfare must be protected by engineers in their professional practice
text_references: Hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public
Engineers shall hold paramount the safety, health, and welfare of the public

label: Employer
description: Organization or individual who employs engineers and to whom engineers owe fiduciary duties as agents or trustees
text_references: Act for each employer or client as faithful agents or trustees
Notify employer or client and appropriate authority if judgment is overruled
Do not disclose client/employer information without consent

label: Client

description: Engineer who works in sales capacity and is permitted to make professional product comparisons

label: Ethical judgment

label: Honesty
description: Capability to exhibit truthfulness and integrity in professional conduct

label: Integrity

label: Objectivity
description: Capability to issue statements and make decisions in an impartial manner

label: Professional development

label: Public safety awareness
description: Capability to prioritize public health, safety, and welfare

label: Error recognition
description: Ability to admit and correct professional mistakes

label: Public safety endangerment
description: Condition where engineering judgment being overruled could endanger life or property

label: Outside area of competence
description: Situation where an engineer lacks the necessary expertise or qualifications for a particular assignment or decision

label: Conflict of interest
description: Situation where personal, financial, or other interests may compromise professional judgment or loyalty to employer/client

label: Confidential information disclosure
description: State involving access to or potential sharing of client/employer confidential or proprietary information

label: Code violation knowledge
description: Condition where an engineer becomes aware of violations of applicable codes, standards, or regulations

label: Multiple compensation arrangement
description: Situation where an engineer receives or may receive compensation from multiple parties for the same work or related services

label: Public decision-making role
description: Condition where an engineer serves in a governmental or public capacity that involves decision-making affecting their private interests

label: Specialized knowledge from previous employment
description: State where an engineer possesses confidential or proprietary knowledge from former employer that could create conflicts in new employment
